caption: I came here last week from NYC and browsed through the mall and decided to try this spot. I ordered the Dinner for Two which consists of 4 empanadas (2 Tampa Girl, 1 Cheeseburger in Paradise, and 1 Buffalo Soldier 2.0), fries, and 2 drinks. Also ordered Tacos Y'all which consists of 2 tacos (1 Chicken and 1 Pork)  and a side of chips and salsa. The cashier was friendly and after you order, you will be handed a food pager that buzzes when your order is ready. At that time, they do not accept cash as they do not have a cash register. It is pretty costly, my bill came up to a little over $40. The tacos were great along with the chips and salsa. The empanadas were tasty, although salty, specifically the Cheeseburger in Paradise. It had a good amount of pickles in  it which gets overwhelming after several bites. Their fries were amazing also their chips and queso which my sister ordered. The wait time was around 10 to 15 minutes. Overall very good.

I had veggie taco but it was one of the worst taco I've ever had in my life so so sorry.  Omg it was super salty! Taste like soy sauce added. It was not like a taco. They also added brussel sprouts and broccoli in it which is really weird. Veggie taco doesn't mean you can add all of irrelevant veggies. You should change veggie taco filling. You can make it with avocado, salsa, grilled mushroom, beans, onion something taste like taco.

Wow!! What an experience.  Had the Empanadas for the first time, and have to say some of the best i have ever had.  I own a restaurant around town and hats off!!  The tacos were on point too, the bang bang chicken taco was an experience in street food with flavors from east asia.  Everything was fresh and on point.

The empanadas are delicious!!! The Tampa Girl in particular was especially tasty! It reminds of a Cuban sandwich--ham, pork, etc.. the texture of the outside was the perfect level of crispy & soft! Also got the queso and that was good too. Ladies working are very friendly and look like they're having a good time! 10/10 would recommend!!
over priced food, not really worth it.
The quesatacos and the sauces they gave were amazing. The flavors were great and the salsa was so fresh too! The staff was super friendly too.

The empanadas are really great and are decently priced. When I go to armature works, this is usually my go to place, unless the line is really long. You can’t go wrong with ordering the cheeseburger empanada, it’s so damn good.
Cheeseburger empanada taste like straight pickles, needs less. Fries are great

I was so excited to try their empanadas, but the one I got ( Tampa Girl) was not good at all. It was super salty, only had ham and cheese ( not all other ingredients listed) and gave me bitter aftertaste. I was very disappointed.

Love this place! The food is so good and super affordable and the atmosphere is so great!!! This is a must go to kind of place if you are planning to be around the Armature Works area. If you like Cubans then order the Tampa Girl 🤤

Horrible experience. Woman who checked me out was extremely rude . No customer appreciation whatsoever. Was told my food was ready and then was yelled at for coming up to get it and sent away to wait longer even after taking my pager. Won’t let you edit anything on their food . Food was ok . Won’t be back or recommending unless they change their staff .
Good food BUT they don’t take cash?!
Empanadas here are super good. My favorite two are the soldier and the burger-like.
Obsessed with this place and their empanadas.
Best empanadas in tampa!  Hands down!
Definitely suggest, Tampa Girl empanadas were great!

Definitely not a place I would not recommend go to, they will not except cash, the lady at the register said they will not take it because of covid, if that is the case, if any if the employee's are going to wear gloves you need to be changing them every time you touch anything, well they were not changing them. To the owner who said I got less than a 5 minute glimpse, I was there a lot longer than 5 minutes, while my wife waited for her food she ordered from you restuarant.  For the numerous times your employees touch different things, your employees didn't change gloves that much. If you are going to make the gloves work, they need yo change their gloves everytime they are touching things, like the buzzers you give out to the customers.  Your employees wipe them off, they grab them with their gloves on and then wipe them off, they should be changing their gloves everytime.
my go-to spot at armature!!

I went to order something and I was asking the girl at the front some questions and then she got her phone call and took it and just sat there near the register talking for like four minutes and ignoring me and I left. Very unprofessional  She was communicating with me and was answering my questions and then suddenly took the call without telling me to hold on. She should have continued answering my questions and put the person on the phone on hold
This restaurant at Armature Works is 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥
Highly recommend the Tampa Girl, absolutely delicious! The food is consistently good each time we've been there and the staff is always super friendly!
Usually very picky with empanadas but I was really happy with theirs. The staff was great, they followed the CDC guidelines for masks and that’s appreciated. Will go again.
Loveeee the empanadas here! The Tampa Girl is my favorite, I’ve ordered multiple times in person and through UberEats, always great. Staff is super friendly and helpful as well.
Won't serve me without a mask? No problem. You won't get my money then.
Ordered 3 empanadas on Uber Eats. I was full after 2. The pastry is very soft and flaky and the filling is very meaty and hearty. I will order again and tell my friends.

Empanadas tasted ok, but over $5 per empanada is way overpriced. That is the most expensive empanada I’ve ever seen, and I’m from a Latin country. I have had other empanadas cheaper and bigger than these.
The food is excellent and the service is always spot on. No matter what you try on the menu, it’s a great choice. It’s by far my favorite place to eat at Armature Works.
Simply the best and a must have!

We ordered through Uber Eats for the first time. The driver couldn't find our apartments and didn't speak English so she cancelled our order. My fiance called the restaurant directly to tell them. The owner remade the food and had an employee deliver directly to us. Not only was the service PHENOMENAL, the food was AMAZING! SO MUCH FLAVOR!! WE WILL BE FREQUENT customers. Thank you guys so much and I pray you are successful!!
Delicious food, courteous staff, and quick service! Very happy their friends King of the Coop are able to host them during this time. Highly recommended (BOTH restaurants)!
Quality of the food is great but pricey for the Quantity. The Cheeseburger empanadas was really good and the bang bang tenders, the tenders needed a dipping sauce for it though.

WOW. Got Uber Eats. It was fantastic. The cheeseburger in paradise was was mouth watering. The tampa girl was one of best takes on a Cuban sandwich I've had in sometime. The Bang bang tenders did not disappoint either. Great fries, chicken and sauce. It was so good i decided to call and review online. That's amazing as an introvert on quarantine...
Delicious veggie tacos!

I've been to Armature Works a few times now and hadn't tried this place yet, but kept hearing good things.  Today, I tried the Cheeseburger in Paradise empanada which was a take on the classic beef and cheese.  Overall, it's a good empanada.  It's VERY cheesy to the point that it almost oozes out when you bite into it.  It almost tastes like one of those cheeseburger pizzas or a cheeseburger Hot Pocket.  I also tried the bang bang shrimp taco as well as the chicken taco.  The bang bang shrimp was way too spicy for me to handle.  I'm a wimp when it comes to spices, but I can usually handle a little heat.  This definitely has a bit of a kick to it, but it ultimately was too much for me.  I almost wish it was a shrimp taco rather than chicken.  It would've been a little lighter and the crunch on it would've been great.  The other chicken taco was good as well; light, fresh, but not a lot of flavor to it.  I tasted mostly the toppings rather than the chicken itself.  The queso was good as well.  A simple white queso, but it didn't have a lot of flavor either.  It needed some heat to it or maybe even some salt.  There's not a lot of options for people who don't eat beef or pork.  I know not everything can be catered to each specific person, but it would've been nice to have a couple more options.  Instead of 3 different varieties of empanadas, maybe there's 5.  Overall, this place has good food.  It could be better though, in my opinion.  It's all good, but it's not something I'd go out of my way for.

$5 dollars for a small empanada is too expensive. I paid $2 extra dollars for chips and queso and there was no queso. I could have went back and asked and the counter, but I walked for 10min trying to find available table to sit.

I ordered a chicken taco and a bang bang taco. The tortilla was so thin and small I couldn’t hold it and eat it with my hands like you would eat a taco. The tortilla was falling apart which made it impossible to hold it. They said it came with chips and for $2 (!!!!!!!) I could add queso. Well, there was no queso. Just some tomatoes chopped up, with no sauce or anything. I couldn’t use the chips to scoop up anything.
Absolutely loved the Tampa Girl empanada. Can’t wait to go back.

I absolutely love this place!! The staff is so welcoming and friendly and the food is mouth watering good. The Tampa Girl is my favorite - highly recommended! The bang bang chicken fingers are also amazing! I usually have to get both when I visit!! I wish I could eat here every day!! 20 out of 5 stars

So far everything I've eaten there was very good, flavorful. Tacos, cheeseburger in paradise, and bang bang chicken. If I had any issue it would be that the food isn't always hot but since it's full of flavor I've overlooked it.
Their Cheeseburger Paradise is better than any regular burger I've had before. Definitely worth eating at and worth coming back to
Highly recommend!! The Tampa Girl is a must!!!

Tried to order a chicken quesadilla for my daughter- even offered to pay more. They flat out refused to make it. They sell cheese quesadillas, they sell chicken, it shouldn’t be that hard to put the two together - still refused. So much for customer service. They have lost a customer forever.
Delicious food and great service. Every suggestion made was good. Waited less than 10 mins on a Saturday which was a plus. Food tasted fresh. Would revisit.
The use to have a cook there couple years or so back. I think her name was Jai or Jolly.  She made the best food!!! The cook they have now is good but not like her.
(Translated by Google) Excellent empanadas, no waste, 100% recommended  (Original) Excelente las empanadas, sin desperdicio, recomendado 100%

Wait times are ridiculously long! I waited 25 minutes for chicken tenders on Wednesday afternoon and didn’t worth it. It was very tough and chewy. When I had the same food a year ago it was much better than this.
Ohhhh emmm Ggggggg. The Tampa girl is the next best invention since the cuban! A cuban empanada... Yes please! They have perfected the empanada. Try it you wont be disappointed.

The bang bang chicken did not disappoint. The sauce has a little heat to it, but is not too bad. The fires were great too. It just runs a little high - $15 for 4 chicken tenders. Definitely could split it between two people. Would go try it if you are a fan on the bonefish bang bang shrimp.
Totally worth visiting. #1 fav is the Tampa Girl empanada. <3
Mmm! Awesome buffalo chicken empanadas!!! We will definitely go back.
First time here.  I had the vegetarian tacos.  The cauliflower in the tacos we're good and crunchy.
Loved it!
the Tampa Girl was amazing
Delicious food and really awesome staff. Cheeseburger and Buffalo empanadas are bomb.
Sorry, but the empanadas are not very good.

I can’t really vouch for their quality of food, but service was atrocious.  Definitely less crowded than a usual Friday, but you wouldn’t know by the wait time.  25 minutes for 2 tacos.  Never going back for this reason alone.

Price is justified due to Armature location. Please give more chicken empanada option where filling is different than the bang bang sauce! (Non pork or beef consumer) overall, I am a returning customer.

Bang Bang Chicken Strips are good, don't think it's worth the money though. Tacos are not consistent. Last time I went they took forever, everyone was getting their food before me, and they were poorly made. Hair in fries, not a good look.
Always a good choice for a bite at armature! Love the bang bang chicken tacos.
Best empanadas and even better service.

Definitely recommend all to eat here. Great food and very friendly staff. I've had practically everything off their menu, and I've yet to be disappointed If you are in Tampa, and craving empanadas or tacos.. check this place out!

Amateur works is a nice location and the vibes are good but the food it’s below mediocre. I was expecting more. It’s nice vibes and looks well but i was expecting a spectacular variety of GOOD tasting food and i tried this place. The service was well. Everyone was nice. The parm and rosemary fries are maxing. Other than that it’s nothing special. The “street corn” was pitiful lol. I was just at the fair and it can’t even compare to that. So don’t waste your time. If you want to relax and get some drinks go. But not for the food.

I've had Empamamas on several occasions and even used them for catering events.  From the brick and mortar at Armature Works to their Food truck, the food, staff, and experience are amazing.  One of the best places in Tampa Bay.  5 stars! (Only because I couldnt add more)
Awesome food with fast and friendly service! Always fresh and hot with lots of options to choose from.  Couldn’t imagine not eating here while at Armature Works.
Great atmosphere, their tacos are awesome.
Best damn empanada I ever had
Can't get enough of their empanadas and tacos.. I swear I can eat them every day
Great experience all around

Best chicken fingers I've ever had!!!... 1,000 Years from now History books will reminisce how good the original Empamama's was! Do yourself a favor and be apart of history and give Empamama's a try today!
Absolutely one of our favorite places to eat in Tampa!

The staff is fantastic and i love everything about Empamamas!! What a fantastic bread delivery system!!! I love love love the Tampa Girl! I love classic Cuban sandwiches but I absolutely can’t get enough of a Cuban sandwich in an empanada! The bang bang chicken is to die for and I just can’t get enough!
Delicious tacos and empanadas! Great service too! Love this place!
NOT VEGAN FRIENDLY. They blantantly lied on the sign, their empanadas are fried in the same oil as animal products. Obviously making them not vegan. Waste of time
